    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_vm.00267.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden</name>
                    <date when="1881-12-11" rend="right">Dec: 11 '81<ptr target="loc.04021_n1"/></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Ruthey</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Yours <choice><abbr>rec'd</abbr><expan>received</expan></choice>&#8212;It seems a friend of mine who is in the <hi rend="underline">Ledger</hi> office Philadelphia,<ptr target="loc.04021_n2"/> <choice><orig>tho't</orig><reg>thought</reg></choice> I was down at Kirkwood&#8212;he was very anxious I should know of the bad illness of a particular friend of mine, &#38; so wrote to Kirkwood&#8212;My friend died Friday morning&#8212;I go to the funeral to-morrow<ptr target="loc.04021_n3"/>&#8212;</p>
            <p>&#8212;I get a little news from you all, once in a while&#8212;(by a visit from Ed some time ago&#8212;&#38; early last week by a visit from Harry.)</p>
            <p>&#8212;<hi rend= "underline">Thank you for the honey</hi>&#8212;it was very acceptable&#8212;we ate every drop of it, &#38; enjoyed it&#8212;it was like the <hi rend="underline">singed cat</hi>&#8212;a great deal better than it <choice><orig>look'd</orig><reg>looked</reg></choice>&#8212;</p>
            <p>&#8212;I am well as usual&#8212;have a little work to do, but not much&#8212;Want to come down &#38; see you all before long&#8212;will write a day or two before<ptr target="loc.04021_n4"/></p>
            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
